Bison has its own test suite. Run 'gmake test' to check if that passes after
you change anything. Currently we have just case 4 failing and it is being
worked on here:

32195707 - Fix test number 4 introduced by bison-3.7.3

Also Bison is used by ON and you can break the ON build process if you change
anything in Bison. You should try building ON on a machine with installed bison.

Before '/opt/onbld/bin/build nightly' you must install the new Bison bits.
